INDICATOR_NAME: Mortality rate, infant, male (per 1,000 live births)
SOURCE_NOTE: Infant mortality rate, male is the number of male infants dying before reaching one year of age, per 1,000 male live births in a given year.
SOURCE_ORGANIZATION: Estimates developed by the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (UNICEF, WHO, World Bank, UN DESA Population Division) at www.childmortality.org.
